{"application": "software-mentions", "version": "0.8.0", "date": "2024-04-15T07:28+0000", "md5": "5A15E517C3ACFB5EEB729306F4AC1DB4", "mentions": [{"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "RoBERTa", "normalizedForm": "RoBERTa", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 7}, "context": "RoBERTa tokenizer is applied in both cases. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.01302194595336914}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 9.715557098388672e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.980232238769531e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9987916946411133}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0008851289749145508}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.980232238769531e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SemEval", "normalizedForm": "SemEval", "offsetStart": 3, "offsetEnd": 10}, "context": "In SemEval'20T11 such labels where merged, and the classes Whataboutism Straw-Men Red-Herring, Bandwagon respectively represent 1.33% and 1.29% of the propagandist messages.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9075902700424194}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.9206275939941406e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.980232238769531e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999858140945435}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.006514489650726318}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.152557373046875e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "PRO-TECT", "normalizedForm": "PRO-TECT", "offsetStart": 4, "offsetEnd": 12}, "context": "The PRO-TECT tool relies on a pipeline architecture to first detect the propaganda text snippets, and second to classify the propaganda text snippets with respect to a specific propaganda technique. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0013657212257385254}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00037676095962524414}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.7881393432617188e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0013657212257385254}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00037676095962524414}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.7881393432617188e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SemEval", "normalizedForm": "SemEval", "offsetStart": 34, "offsetEnd": 41}, "context": "The systems that took part in the SemEval 2020 Challenge -Task 11 represent the most recent approaches to identify propaganda techniques based on given propagandist spans.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.679125189781189}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0023005008697509766}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.7881393432617188e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999858140945435}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.006514489650726318}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.152557373046875e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Text dEteCTion", "normalizedForm": "Text dEteCTion", "offsetStart": 47, "offsetEnd": 61}, "context": "In this paper, we present PRO-TECT (PROpaganda Text dEteCTion), a new system to automatically detect propagandist messages and classify them along with the propaganda techniques employed.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 6.74128532409668e-05}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999272227287292}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.980232238769531e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 6.74128532409668e-05}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999272227287292}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.980232238769531e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "RoBERTa", "normalizedForm": "RoBERTa", "offsetStart": 48, "offsetEnd": 55}, "context": "To combine the results from sentence-span based RoBERTa with the feature-based BiLSTM we apply the joint loss strategy proposed in (Vorakitphan et al., 2021).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9987916946411133}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0008851289749145508}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.980232238769531e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9987916946411133}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0008851289749145508}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.980232238769531e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SemEval", "normalizedForm": "SemEval", "offsetStart": 87, "offsetEnd": 94}, "context": "Then, it classifies propagandist tokens according to the 14 propaganda categories from SemEval task (T11).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.2937083840370178}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.3053417205810547e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.980232238769531e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999858140945435}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.006514489650726318}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.152557373046875e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Text dEteCTion", "normalizedForm": "Text dEteCTion", "offsetStart": 95, "offsetEnd": 109}, "context": "To achieve this ambitious goal, we present in this paper a new tool called PROTECT (PROpaganda Text dEteCTion) to automatically identify and classify propaganda in texts. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 5.942583084106445e-05}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999114871025085}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.980232238769531e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 6.74128532409668e-05}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999272227287292}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.980232238769531e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "RoBERTa", "normalizedForm": "RoBERTa", "offsetStart": 105, "offsetEnd": 112}, "context": "More specifically, both the tokenized sentence and the span are used to feed the transformer-based model RoBERTa (robertabase pre-trained model) 7 (Liu et al., 2019) to per- 6 We are aware that sigmoid function is usually used as default activation function in binary classification.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.987098753452301}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.0728836059570312e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9987916946411133}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0008851289749145508}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.980232238769531e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "RoBERTa", "normalizedForm": "RoBERTa", "offsetStart": 119, "offsetEnd": 126}, "context": "where each loss value is produced from CrossEntropy function of its classifier (e.g., loss sentence and loss span from RoBERTa models of sentence and span, loss semantic argumentation features from the BiLSTM model.)", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8602219820022583}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.3828277587890625e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9987916946411133}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0008851289749145508}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.980232238769531e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SemEval", "normalizedForm": "SemEval", "offsetStart": 169, "offsetEnd": 176}, "context": "More precisely: i) we input a sentence to the tokenizer where max length is set to 128 with padding; ii) we input the span provided by the propaganda span-template from SemEval T11 dataset, and we set max length value of 20 with padding.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999858140945435}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 4.291534423828125e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999858140945435}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.006514489650726318}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.152557373046875e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SemEval", "normalizedForm": "SemEval", "offsetStart": 181, "offsetEnd": 188}, "context": "To evaluate the approach on which PROTECT relies, we use two standard benchmarks for Propaganda Detection and Classification, namely the NLP4IF'19 (Da San Martino et al., 2019) and SemEval'20 datasets (Da San Martino et al., 2020a Those classes are not uniformly distributed in the data sets.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.7924078106880188}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 5.9604644775390625e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999858140945435}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.006514489650726318}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.152557373046875e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SemEval", "normalizedForm": "SemEval", "offsetStart": 266, "offsetEnd": 273}, "context": "Such features proved to be useful to improve the performances of our approach on propagandist messages classification, obtaining SoTA results on some categories (in (Vorakitphan et al., 2021) we provide a comparison of our model with SoTA systems on both NLP4IF and SemEval datasets).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.29222774505615234}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.006514489650726318}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999858140945435}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.006514489650726318}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.152557373046875e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SemEval", "normalizedForm": "SemEval", "offsetStart": 299, "offsetEnd": 306}, "context": "The output of the snippet detection task (Step 1) are provided as a span-pattern to the models performing Step 2. Table 1 reports on the obtained results of the full pipeline (Step 1+Step 2) averaged over 5 runs (we cannot provide a fair comparison of those results with SoTA systems, given that in SemEval the two tasks are separately evaluated and no pipeline results are provided). ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9982253909111023}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 3.2186508178710938e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.152557373046875e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999858140945435}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.006514489650726318}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.152557373046875e-07}}}], "references": [], "runtime": 58894, "id": "df7d14a04d3e6740c82362531f12325defb3fd25", "metadata": {"id": "df7d14a04d3e6740c82362531f12325defb3fd25"}, "original_file_path": "../../datalake/Samuel/SOFTware-Sync/data/xml_not_sofctied/hal-03417019.grobid.tei.xml", "file_name": "hal-03417019.grobid.tei.xml"}